content:
The core library contains a few uses of the precedence command. What does this do? Register a token? The precedence always seems to be 0.

Example from init/meta/interactive:

precedence `generalizing` : 0

Yes, it registers a token. The canonical reference documentation is in the precedence_cmd function in notation_cmd.cpp.
There is also reserve notation `generalizing` which does something similar (but I can't tell you what it does exactly).
